28/08/2006
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- An international seminar on human trafficking opens on Monday (28 August) in Podgorica, organised by the Stability Pact and the governments of Norway, Britain, Slovenia and Switzerland.
Representatives of respective police authorities from all Southeast European countries and UNMIK are participating in debates on the creation of a Balkan network for fighting organised crime.
In other news, a moderate earthquake rattled part of southern Montenegro on Saturday.
The 4.2 magnitude quake had an epicentre at Mount Rumija near the border with Albania.
No injuries or damage were reported.
(MINA, Focus, Fena - 27/08/06)
